Privately I have no belief that this “Jamaica Comittee,” with all its noises, will ever get to anything of practical. By a late glance I accidentally had into the heart of their affairs, it appears that, to venture on this precious “Prosecution,” they imperatively needed £10,000,—and had not, so far as I cd judge, the slightest chance to get it.The Jamaica Committee (see 
TC to HH, 23 Aug.

) published a statement in the Daily News, 12 Oct., addressed “to their friends throughout the country” in which they “resolved to undertake the duty which the government had declined, of submitting to judicial investigation the conduct of Governor Eyre and his subordinates in putting to death Mr. Gordon and other British subjects for treason, sedition, and other alleged offences without a lawful trial.” The Committee explained that the legal process, “owing to the distance of Jamaica and other circumstances, will be very expensive; and it is evident that the committee will have to encounter a powerful resistance backed by all the resources of wealth. They deem it necessary, therefore, to appeal to the public to raise the fund to £10,000.”
 At that date, after all this bellowing   shrieking from the Friends of Humanity in mass, the sum actually on hand was £475 some shillings   some pence.TC’s source for these figures is unknown. John Stuart Mill reported to a friend, 4 Oct.: “when I last heard from the Cm they had raised £3200 though no appeal had yet been made to the general public. It must be considerably more now;   I have good hopes that we shall be near enough to getting the £11866 we ask for” (Mineka 3:1206); and Hamilton Hume quoted a report from the Morning Star, 12 Oct.: “The subscriptions and guarantees already received have justified the [Jamaica] Committee in taking the first steps; and they hope by the time the courts resume their sittings, to be in possession of the opinion of eminent counsel as to the form of indictment and method of procedure” (Eyre Defence and Aid Fund 3); TC would have seen this as he helped Hume with the pamphlet proofs; see 
