Disraeli, Benjamin (Dizzy) (1804–81; 
ODNB
), politician and novelist, Chancellor of the Exchequer 1867–68.

Eyre, Edward John (1815–1901; 
ODNB
), farmer, explorer, and colonial administrator in Australia and New Zealand 1832–53; colonial administrator in various Caribbean islands 1854–60; governor of Jamaica 1862–65. He m., 1850, Adelaide Fanny, b. Ormond (ca. 1826–1905); they had six children: Gervas Selwyn (1851–1920), Edward Broughton (1853—after 1911), Ada Austin (ca. 1855–1929), Charles Ormond (1856—ca. 1924), Henry (1861—after 1901), May Lillian (1865–1940), and Sydney Frederick (1871–1929).

Forster, John (“Fuz”) (1812–76; 
ODNB
; see 
