Froude, James Anthony (1818–94; 
ODNB
), journalist and historian, ed. of Fraser’s Magazine
1860–74; he m., first, 1849, Charlotte Maria, b. Grenfell (1812–60); they had two das., Georgina Margaret (1850–1935) and Rose Mary (b. 1852), and a son, Pascall Grenfell (1854–79). He m., second, 1861, Henrietta Elizabeth, b. Warre (1824–74); they had a son, Ashley Anthony (1863–1949), and a da., May (b. 1867). They lived at 5 Onslow Gdns., Fulham Rd. Henrietta’s father, John Ashley Warre (1787–1860), had m., as his third wife, Charlotte Froude’s sister Caroline Grenfell (1809–86), and her sister Frances Eliza Grenfell m. Charles Kingsley (see below).

Gladstone, William Ewart (1809–98; 
ODNB
), politician, Chancellor of the Exchequer 1859–66; leader of the liberal party 1867–74. He m., 1839, Catherine, b. Glynne (1812–1900; 
ODNB
).

Hume, Hamilton (1838–72), author and journalist; previously a lieutenant in the Crimea and India; sec. of the Eyre Defence and Aid Fund. He m., 1865, Elizabeth, b. Harris (b. ca. 1842), and had two children, Hamilton (b. 1870) and Denham (b. 1872). In library catalogs he is often confused with [Alexander] Hamilton Hume (1797–1873; 
ODNB
), Australian explorer, who lived entirely in Australia and who did not publish.

